    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-01-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="247" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hicks</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-01-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 15,
                                1890</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 28.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 56, of December 20,
                            1889, in relation to the claim of the Hydrographic Commission of the
                            Amazon, has been received.</p>
                <p>The situation has been made known to Mr. Shands, who represents the
                            claimants.</p>
                <p>I am, etc,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
